dplyr - case_when (+ sort)
========================================================
class: small-code
```{r }
df_cars_limited %>% 
  mutate(Pow= case_when( hp>200 & cyl>=8 ~ 'Strong', 
                     TRUE ~ 'Weak') ) %>%
  arrange(hp)
```
mutate vs. summarize
========================================================
`mutate` adds a column but keeps same # rows

`summarize` adds a column but reduces the rows down to one row per unique group

